    • Method Detail

      • resetRegister

        public void resetRegister()
        Reset signature engine to register.
        All registered signature will be removed.
        See Also:
        register(ArrayList)

      • register

        public void register(ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> signature)
              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Register a signature.
        You should register at least 3 signatures to lock the file with signature.
        Parameters:
        signature - The strokes of signature
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if signature is null or has any object which is not an SpenObjectStroke. Or, if an SpenObjectStroke doens't have orientations or tilts information.
        Thrown if you register 20 signatures already.
        Or, thrown if it is failed to register.
        Since:
        4.0.0
        See Also:
        resetRegister(), getRegisteredCount()

      • lock

        public void lock()
          throws IOException,
                 SpenUnsupportedTypeException
        Lock(encrypt) the specified file with registered signature.
        You should register at least 3 signatures to lock the file.
        Throws:
        IOException - Thrown if the file which is you set when you create this instance is not found, or if a temporary directory cannot be created.
        SpenUnsupportedTypeException - Thrown if the file is not in SPD file format.
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the file which is you set when you create this instance is locked already.
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the number of registered signatures is not enough.
        Since:
        4.0.0
        See Also:
        register(ArrayList), unlock(ArrayList)

      • unlock

        public void unlock(ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> signature)
            throws IOException,
                   SpenInvalidPasswordException,
                   SpenUnsupportedTypeException
        Unlock(decrypt) the specified file which is locked by signature.
        Parameters:
        signature - The signature to unlock the file.
        Throws:
        IOException - Thrown if the cache directory cannot be created or the file is not found.
        SpenInvalidPasswordException - Thrown if the signature is wrong.
        SpenUnsupportedTypeException - Thrown if the file is not in SPD file format.
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if signature is null or has any object which is not an SpenObjectStroke. Or, if an SpenObjectStroke doens't have orientations or tilts information.
        Since:
        4.0.0
        See Also:
        lock(), isLocked(String)

      • isLocked

        public static boolean isLocked(String filePath)
        Check whether the file is locked(encrypted) by signature or not.
        Parameters:
        filePath - The absolute path of the file.
        Returns:
        true, if the file is locked by signature.
        false, if the file is not locked by signature.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if it is failed to load signature libraries
        Since:
        4.0.0
        See Also:
        lock(), unlock(ArrayList)
